---
Source:
  - Title: The Essential Mystics, Poets, Saints and Sages
    ISBN: 978-1571746931
By: P'ang Yun
Page: 174
---
The mind has no substance in itself,
but is like a reflection in a mirror.
Once clear sight comes,
all that seems separate in the world
is recognized to be One.
The will -- the ego -- must die,
and once it is dead,
one will have peace of mind.
